cerial.format.alignmentScope.markdownDescription:
Alignment scope for field decorators.

- **`group`** — Align within each model/object block independently:
  ```
  model User {
    id    Record @id
    email Email  @unique
  }
  model Post {
    id        Record @id
    createdAt Date   @createdAt
  }
  ```
- **`block`** — Align across all blocks in the file:
  ```
  model User {
    id        Record @id
    email     Email  @unique
  }
  model Post {
    id        Record @id
    createdAt Date   @createdAt
  }
  ```

cerial.format.blockSeparation.markdownDescription:
Blank lines between top-level blocks (models, objects, enums).

- **`2`** — Two blank lines between blocks:
  ```
  model User {
    id Record @id
  }


  model Post {
    id Record @id
  }
  ```
- **`1`** — One blank line between blocks:
  ```
  model User {
    id Record @id
  }

  model Post {
    id Record @id
  }
  ```
- **`honor`** — Preserve existing separation from source

cerial.format.indentSize.markdownDescription:
Indentation size for formatted output.

- **`2`** — Two spaces:
  ```
  model User {
    id Record @id
  }
  ```
- **`4`** — Four spaces:
  ```
  model User {
      id Record @id
  }
  ```
- **`tab`** — Tab character:
  ```
  model User {
  	id Record @id
  }
  ```

cerial.format.commentStyle.markdownDescription:
Comment style normalization.

- **`honor`** — Preserve existing comment style as-is
- **`hash`** — Convert all comments to `#` style:
  ```
  # this is a comment
  model User {
    id Record @id # inline comment
  }
  ```
- **`slash`** — Convert all comments to `//` style:
  ```
  // this is a comment
  model User {
    id Record @id // inline comment
  }
  ```
